verses.text:
And the priests’ custom with the people \add was, that\add*,
when any man offered sacrifice, the priest’s servant came, while the
flesh was in seething, with a fleshhook of three teeth in his hand;

And it came to pass at that time, when Eli \add was\add* laid
down in his place, and his eyes began to wax dim, \add that\add*
he could not see;

And the Philistines fought, and Israel was smitten, and they
fled every man into his tent: and there was a very great slaughter;
for there fell of Israel thirty thousand footmen.

And these \add are\add* the golden emerods which the Philistines
returned \add for\add* a trespass offering unto the \nd LORD\nd*;
for Ashdod one, for Gaza one, for Askelon one, for Gath one, for
Ekron one;

And they sent messengers to the inhabitants of Kirjath-jearim,
saying, The Philistines have brought again the ark of the \nd LORD\nd*;
come ye down, \add and\add* fetch it up to you.

And Saul tarried in the uttermost part of Gibeah under a pomegranate
tree which \add is\add* in Migron: and the people that \add were\add* with him
\add were\add* about six hundred men;

And the staff of his spear \add was\add* like a weaver’s beam;
and his spear’s head \add weighed\add* six hundred shekels of iron:
and one bearing a shield went before him.

And Jesse said unto David his son, Take now for thy brethren
an ephah of this parched \add corn\add*, and these ten loaves, and
run to the camp to thy brethren;

And Saul sought to smite David even to the wall with the javelin;
but he slipped away out of Saul’s presence, and he smote the javelin
into the wall: and David fled, and escaped that night.

And the prophet Gad said unto David, Abide not in the hold;
depart, and get thee into the land of Judah. Then David departed,
and came into the forest of Hareth.

And it shall come to pass, when the \nd LORD\nd* shall have
done to my lord according to all the good that he hath spoken concerning thee, and shall have
appointed thee ruler over Israel;

And it came to pass, when David and his men were come to Ziklag
on the third day, that the Amalekites had invaded the south, and
Ziklag, and smitten Ziklag, and burned it with fire;

And they found an Egyptian in the field, and brought him to
David, and gave him bread, and he did eat; and they made him drink
water;

And the Philistines followed hard upon Saul and upon his sons;
and the Philistines slew Jonathan, and Abinadab, and Malchi-shua,
Saul’s sons.
